The paper discusses the design of an intelligent interactive interface for folksonomies, which involves human-computer interaction and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the need for tools to resolve ambiguity in definitions, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the visualization and exploitation of folksonomies in web applications, which could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), and databases (cs.DB).
